# tc-pipelines CODEOWNERS — the org's CI + deploy control plane.
#
# A code-owner review is required ONLY for a PR that touches one of the paths
# below. Everything else (README, CHANGELOG, prose docs) auto-merges on green
# once the "main" ruleset drops required approvals to 0 with code-owner review
# left ON. This is the org standard: governance/config needs a human; routine
# work merges itself.
#
# Owner is @quanyeomans (matching the sibling control-plane repo tc-fitness):
# the reusable workflows and composite actions here are consumed by every repo
# in the org, so a change to them is the highest-blast-radius edit we make.

# The reusable workflows + composite actions every repo consumes.
/.github/                @quanyeomans
/actions/                @quanyeomans

# The canonical standards, rulesets, skeletons, and the bootstrap script.
/governance/             @quanyeomans

# Deploy + tooling that acts on live infrastructure.
/infra/                  @quanyeomans
/tools/                  @quanyeomans

# The repo's own gate config + dependency pins.
/pyproject.toml          @quanyeomans
/uv.lock                 @quanyeomans

# CODEOWNERS governs itself.
/CODEOWNERS              @quanyeomans
/.github/CODEOWNERS      @quanyeomans
